description: Look at Life: Civil Aviation in the 60s History, Technology Documentary hosted by Rob Curling and Tim Turner, published by Carlton Media in 2003 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/3/3a/Look-at-Life-Civil-Aviation-in-the-60s-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Fly back in time with this nostalgic compilation of films from the 1960s! Look at Life was a regular British series of short documentary films of which over 500 were produced between 1959 and 1968 by the Special Features Division of the Rank Organisation. Films included are AIR HOSTESS (1960), CONTROLLED LANDING (1961), CITY OF THE AIR (1963), FLYING TO WORK (1964), THE SPIRIT OF BROOKLANDS (1965) and THE BIG TAKE OFF (1967).
